data.enText: the act of accepting sb into an institution, organization, etc.; the right to enter a place or to join an institution or organization
data.chText: （机构、组织等的）准许加入，加入权，进入权

data.enText: Hospital admission is not necessary in most cases.
data.chText: 大多数情况下，病人无须住院。

data.enText: Hospital admissions for asthma attacks have doubled.
data.chText: 哮喘发作入院人次已成倍增加。

data.enText: countries applying for admission to the European Union
data.chText: 申请加入欧洲联盟的国家
大学招生政策 / 招生办公室

data.enText: Last admissions to the park are at 4 p.m.
data.chText: 公园最晚的入园时间是下午4点。

data.enText: They tried to get into the club but were refused admission.
data.chText: 他们试图进入俱乐部，但遭到拒绝。

data.enText: She failed to gain admission to the university of her choice.
data.chText: 她未获自己选择的大学录取。

data.enText: a statement in which sb admits that sth is true, especially sth wrong or bad that they have done
data.chText: （尤指对过错、罪行的）承认，招认，招供
承认有罪 / 失败 / 被击败

data.enText: The minister's resignation was an admission that she had lied.
data.chText: 这位部长辞职等于承认她自己撒过谎。

data.enText: He is a thief by his own admission (= he has admitted it) .
the amount of money that you pay to go into a building or to an event

word_means: 准许加入，加入权，进入权
simple_means.memory_skill: ad- 加强 + miss 送出,投掷 + -ion 行为,状态

means: (尤指对过错、罪行的)承认，招认，招供
(机构、组织等的)准许加入，加入权，进入权

ex.enText: He is one of those applying for admission to university.
ex.chText: 他是大学入学申请者之一。

ex.enText: When did she gain admission to the club?
ex.chText: 她是何时获准加入这家俱乐部的？

synonyms.bx: 指允许某人进入某一建筑物或场所，或成为学校、俱乐部等的成员。

ex.enText: All the tickets were sold out, so I was unable to gain admittance.
ex.chText: 票都卖完了，我无法进场。

synonyms.bx: 指进入某建筑物、机构等的权利。

ex.enText: Is entry to the garden included?
ex.chText: 包含进入花园的费用吗？

ex.enText: Why were the refugees repeatedly refused entry into the country?
ex.chText: 为什么难民进入该国的请求一再遭到拒绝？

synonyms.bx: 通常指进入具体场所的权利，常后接介词 to/into。

tr: the act of admitting someone to enter
example: the surgery was performed on his second admission to the clinic

tr: an acknowledgment of the truth of something

example.ex: Students apply for admission to a particular college...
example.tran: 学生们申请上某所大学。

example.ex: Poland and Czechoslovakia have vigorously pursued admission to the European Community...
example.tran: 波兰和捷克斯洛伐克已经积极寻求加入欧共体。

example.ex: ...an increase in hospital admissions of children.

value.def: Admission is permission given to a person to enter a place, or permission given to a country to enter an organization. Admission is also the act of entering a place.
value.tran: 准许进入；准许加入；进入；加入

example.ex: Each school sets its own admissions policy.
example.tran: 每所学校制定各自的录取政策。

value.def: Admissions to a place such as a school or university are the people who are allowed to enter or join it.

example.ex: Gates open at 10.30am and admission is free.

posc.def: Admission is also used before a noun.

example.ex: The admission price is $8 for adults.

value.def: Admission at a park, museum, or other place is the amount of money that you pay to enter it.

example.ex: By his own admission, he is not playing well...
She wanted some admission of guilt from her father.
example.tran: 她期待她父亲能够认罪。

value.def: An admission is a statement that something bad, unpleasant, or embarrassing is true.
